		  <td width="603" bgcolor="#DE6926"><p align="justify"><strong>&quot;<span class="style3">This book of the law shall not depart out of thy mouth; but thou shalt meditate therein day and night, that thou mayest observe to do according to all that is written therein: for then thou shalt make thy way prosperous, and then thou shalt have good success&quot; (Joshua  1:8).</span> </strong></p>
			  
			<p align="justify" class="style18"> </p>
			<p align="justify" class="style18">Your Quiet Time Companion. </p>
			<p><img src="holy.JPG" width="244" height="197" />
				  2013/03/19<br />			  <strong><br />
			  </strong><span class="style3 style18"><strong>Today's Topic</strong></span><strong><span class="style18">: </span>CALLED TO BE FISHERS OF MEN </strong></p>
			<p align="justify" class="style28"><strong>HAPPY NEW YEAR </strong></p>
			<p><strong>Matthew 4:12-25</strong></p>
			<p><strong>&nbsp;After Herod had arrested John, Jesus left Nazareth and lived in the region of Galilee  [vs.12-13] not out fear anyway. Matthew reveals that by doing ministry in  Zebulum and Naphtali, Jesus filled Isaiah&rsquo;s prophecy [vs.14-16; Is 9:1-2]. Jesus and John preached the same  message [Matt.3;2] which incidentally, is hardly preached today. &lsquo;Repentance&rsquo;  remains the core of the gospel message. See Acts2;38-39; 3;19. When people repent,  their sins are forgiven and God&rsquo;s reign over their lives begins. By his  preaching and healing, Jesus announced that God&rsquo;s reign was nearer.<br />
	  The first four men Jesus called to  follow him were fishermen [vs.18-22]. Their new calling was to be fishers of  men [v.19].As disciples of Jesus Christ, we are called to be fishers of men  [Mk. 16:15]. Just as they left all to follow Jesus, no matter the cost.<br />
	  Note that the three components of  Jesus ministry are for us also [v.23].News of his ministry spread far and wide  though there was no multimedia equipment in those days. Then how was it done  even today, one person telling another is an effective way of spreading the  good news of God&rsquo;s reign in people&rsquo;s lives. Are you a fisher of humans?<br />
	  Prayer: Make me a fisher of humans,  Lord Jesus, and help me to follow you all the days of my life, no matter the  cost.</strong></p>
			<p align="justify" class="style25">&nbsp;</p>
			<p class="style2"><strong>Motivational quotes for the week:</strong></p>
			<p align="center" class="style2 style25"><strong>&quot;I challenge you to make your life a masterpiece. I challenge you to join the
			  ranks of those people who live what they teach, who walk their talk.<br />
			~ ~ Anthony Robbins</strong></p>
			<p><strong>To promote the spread of God's word, please kindly send an email to us with any christian audio or video message, picture, songs, journals
			and ebooks along with its discription. Or you can send to us a testimony. God Bless You. Amen</strong></p>
